HEADWORD: Passiveness
<hw>Pas"sive*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
passive; unresisting submission.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To be an effect implies <qex>passiveness</qex>, or the being
subject to the power and action of its cause.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Edwards.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>passivism</ent>⟦br⟧
